  <name>Nova Design</name>
  <summary>Linux CAD/BIM light for trades</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Nova Design is a Linux-only CAD/BIM application focused on trades work such as electrical, plumbing, masonry, drywall, and painting. Built in Rust with GTK4 and Libadwaita, it provides a modern, efficient workflow for trade professionals.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Multi-discipline support (electrical, plumbing, drywall, etc.)</li>
      <li>Bill of Materials (BOM) calculations</li>
      <li>Phase-based design (existing, demolition, new)</li>
      <li>Symbol libraries for electrical and plumbing components</li>
      <li>Layer management by discipline</li>
      <li>Material database and cost calculations</li>
      <li>Plugin system for extensibility</li>
      <li>Internationalization (Italian and English)</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.nova.Design.desktop</launchable>
